    "description": "iRidge, Inc. engages in the application, business production, and fintech businesses in Japan. The company plans, develops, and supports the operation of smartphone applications; provides end-to-end support from formulating business strategies and digital transformation strategies to service development; and plans, develops, and operates the digital local currency platform MoneyEasy. It also provides APPBOX, an app business platform that is premised on linking with external systems and various third-party tools; APPBOX partner program; and app planning/RFP support services. In addition, the company offers LINE mini app development, including scratch and Kit-Curu; app marketing tools, such as FANSHIP; and assignment management solution comprising Co-Assign. Further, it provides consulting services, including app growth support, ASO support, UX research, and business production support services; and other solutions comprising DX and GX solutions. The company was incorporated in 2008 and is based in Minato, Japan."
